## K-Means Clustering

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
In[4]:
# Load PCA Data
df_pca = pd.read_csv("../data/train_pca_features.csv")
X_pca = df_pca[["PCA1", "PCA2"]]
In[6]:
# Run K-Means
# Choose k=2 since we have binary satisfaction (unsatisfied/satisfied)
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=42)
kmeans_labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X_pca)

# Add cluster assignments to the dataframe
df_pca["KMeans_Cluster"] = kmeans_labels
In[8]:
# Evaluate Clustering
sil_score = silhouette_score(X_pca, kmeans_labels)
print(f"Silhouette Score: {sil_score:.4f}")

Silhouette Score: 0.4140
In[12]:
# Visualize Clusters
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df_pca, x="PCA1", y="PCA2", hue="KMeans_Cluster", palette="Set2")
plt.title("K-Means Clustering (k=2) on PCA-Reduced Data")
plt.show()
In[16]:
#Compare Clusters vs Satisfaction
comparison = pd.crosstab(df_pca["satisfaction"], df_pca["KMeans_Cluster"])
print(comparison)

## DBSCAN on PCA-Reduced Data

from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN

df_pca = pd.read_csv("../data/train_pca_features.csv")
X_pca = df_pca[["PCA1", "PCA2"]]

# Run DBSCAN
dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=0.5, min_samples=10)
dbscan_labels = dbscan.fit_predict(X_pca)

# Add cluster assignments (noise = -1)
df_pca["DBSCAN_Cluster"] = dbscan_labels
# Label -1 indicates noise points (outliers)
In[27]:
# Evaluate (Only If >1 Cluster)
# Filter out noise for silhouette score
mask = dbscan_labels != -1
if len(set(dbscan_labels)) > 1:
    sil_score = silhouette_score(X_pca[mask], dbscan_labels[mask])
    print(f"Silhouette Score (excluding noise): {sil_score:.4f}")
else:
    print("Only one cluster found. Silhouette score not applicable.")

Only one cluster found. Silhouette score not applicable.

plt.title("DBSCAN Clustering on PCA-Reduced Data")
plt.legend(title="Cluster")
plt.show()

## Agglomerative Clustering on PCA Data

from sklearn.cluster import AgglomerativeClustering
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

df_pca = pd.read_csv("../data/train_pca_features.csv")
# Limit the dataset to 2,000 points
sample_df = df_pca.sample(n=2000, random_state=42)
X_sample = sample_df[["PCA1", "PCA2"]]

# Fit Agglomerative Clustering (k=2)
agglo = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=2, linkage='ward')
agglo_labels = agglo.fit_predict(X_sample)

# Add cluster labels to the sampled dataframe
sample_df["Agglo_Cluster"] = agglo_labels
In[20]:
# Evaluate (Silhouette Score)
sil_score = silhouette_score(X_sample, agglo_labels)
print(f"Silhouette Score: {sil_score:.4f}")

Silhouette Score: 0.3744
In[22]:
# Visualize Clusters
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=sample_df, x="PCA1", y="PCA2", hue="Agglo_Cluster", palette="Set1")
plt.title("Agglomerative Clustering (Sampled, k=2)")
plt.legend(title="Cluster")
plt.show()
In[]:
# Unlike KMeans or supervised models, AgglomerativeClustering does not have a .predict() method. 
# Once trained, it cant predict new labels for user input in the UI.

## GMM Clustering on PCA-Reduced Data

from sklearn.mixture import GaussianMixture

df_pca = pd.read_csv("../data/train_pca_features.csv")
X_pca = df_pca[["PCA1", "PCA2"]]

# Train GMM
gmm = GaussianMixture(n_components=2, covariance_type='full', random_state=42)
gmm.fit(X_pca)

# Predict hard cluster labels
gmm_labels = gmm.predict(X_pca)

# Add to DataFrame
df_pca["GMM_Cluster"] = gmm_labels
In[28]:
# Evaluate Silhouette Score
sil_score = silhouette_score(X_pca, gmm_labels)
print(f"Silhouette Score: {sil_score:.4f}")

Silhouette Score: 0.4048

plt.legend(title="Cluster")
plt.show()

### visualize the unsupervised models metrics ###

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Create a DataFrame for unsupervised model metrics
unsupervised_metrics = pd.DataFrame({
    "Model": [
        "K-Means", 
        "DBSCAN", 
        "Agglomerative", 
        "GMM", 
        "Spectral Clustering"
    ],
    "Silhouette Score": [
        0.4140, 
        None,        # DBSCAN only found one cluster
        0.3744, 
        0.4048, 
        0.0596
    ],
    "Notes": [
        "Performed well with distinct clusters",
        "Only one cluster found",
        "Reasonable separation on sample",
        "Good separation, slightly less than KMeans",
        "Failed to form distinct clusters"
    ]
})

# Display the DataFrame
print("Unsupervised Clustering Model Summary:\n")
print(unsupervised_metrics.to_string(index=False))

# Plot Silhouette Scores (excluding None)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(
    data=unsupervised_metrics[unsupervised_metrics["Silhouette Score"].notnull()],
    x="Model",
    y="Silhouette Score",
    palette="crest"
)
plt.title("Silhouette Scores of Unsupervised Clustering Models")
plt.ylim(0, 0.5)
plt.xticks(rotation=30)
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
